# No Hardcoded Secrets or Environment-Specific URLs

Never hardcode credentials, API keys, tokens, or environment-specific URLs in source code. Always read them from environment variables.

## Rules

- No secrets (passwords, API keys, tokens, connection strings) in code, tests, or committed config.
- No environment-specific URLs (e.g. `http://localhost:3001`, prod hostnames) hardcoded; read them from env vars.
- Provide sane non-secret defaults only for local development.
- Document new variables in `.env.example` and never commit real `.env` files.

## Examples

```typescript
// ❌ BAD
const apiKey = "sk_live_abc123";
const baseUrl = "https://api.prod.example.com";

// ✅ GOOD
const apiKey = process.env.API_KEY;
if (!apiKey) throw new Error("API_KEY is not set");

const baseUrl = process.env.API_BASE_URL ?? "http://localhost:3001";
```
